{{Infobox philosopher |region = [[Western philosophy]] |era = [[Contemporary philosophy|21st-century philosophy]] |color = |image = |name = '''Henry Shue''' |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|mf=yes|1940|3|24}} |birth_place = |death_date = |death_place = |school_tradition = [[Analytic philosophy|Analytic]] | institutions = [[Merton College]] |main_interests = [[political philosophy]], [[moral philosophy]] | thesis_title = | thesis_url = | thesis_year = | doctoral_advisor = | doctoral_students = [[Seth Lazar]] |notable_ideas = | spouse = | education = | alma_mater = |influences = |awards = |website = }}
'''Henry Shue''' is an American philosopher, Professor Emeritus of Politics and International Relations at [[Merton College]] of [[University of Oxford|Oxford University]]. Previously he was [[Wyn and William Y Hutchinson]] Professor of Ethics & Public Life at [[Cornell University]]. Shue is best known for his book, ''[[Basic Rights: Subsistence, Affluence, and U.S. Foreign Policy]]''.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Payne |first1=Michael |title=Henry Shue on Basic Rights |journal=[[Essays in Philosophy]] |date=June 2008 |volume=9 |issue=2 |url=https://commons.pacificu.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?referer=&httpsredir=1&article=1317&context=eip |accessdate=21 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Kiper |first1=Jordan |title=Henry Shue on Basic Rights: A Defense |journal=[[Human Rights Review]] |date=2 April 2011 |volume=12 |issue=4 |pages=505–514 |doi=10.1007/s12142-011-0197-8 |url=https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s12142-011-0197-8 |accessdate=21 August 2018 |language=en |issn=1524-8879}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Wellman |first1=Carl |title=Review of Basic Rights |journal=[[Human Rights Quarterly]] |date=1981 |volume=3 |issue=3 |pages=144–147 |doi=10.2307/761904 |url=https://www.jstor.org/stable/761904?seq=1#page_scan_tab_contents |accessdate=21 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Ashford |first1=Elizabeth |title=In What Sense Is the Right to Subsistence a Basic Right? |journal=[[Journal of Social Philosophy]] |date=December 2009 |volume=40 |issue=4 |pages=488–503 |doi=10.1111/j.1467-9833.2009.01467.x |url=https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/pdf/10.1111/j.1467-9833.2009.01467.x |accessdate=21 August 2018 |language=en |issn=0047-2786}}</ref>
