{{Nihongo|'''Shōfuku-ji'''|聖福寺}} is an [[Ōbaku]] [[Zen]] temple in [[Nagasaki, Nagasaki|Nagasaki]], [[Nagasaki prefecture|Nagasaki]], [[Japan]].  Its honorary ''[[Buddhist temples in Japan#sangō|sangō]]'' prefix is {{nihongo|''Manjusan''|万寿山}}. It was founded by [[Tetsushin Dōhan]], the grandson of [[Ingen]], with support from [[Nagasaki bugyō]] and Chinese merchants, and construction was completed in 1677.

